The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 India tops Bose sound chart in Asia

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, Oct. 17: India is the fastest growing market for Bose Corporation in Asia. The market has increased at more than 60 per cent year-on-year compared with countries like China, which recorded a 20 per cent growth annually.

 India is one of the highest growing markets as more cities and town have demand for Bose products. Our professional systems division, which was set up initially to provide customised sound solutions for institutions, has to focus more on home and personal audio systems, which now contribute 60 per cent to the companys revenues in the country, said Ratish Pandey, country head, Bose Corporation. 




